The '''1862 [[Constitution]] of [[Liechtenstein]]''' was signed into law by [[Johann II, Prince of Liechtenstein]] on September 26 at [[Lednice|Eisgrub]], [[Moravia]]. It was heavily influenced by the constitutions of [[Vorarlberg]] (1861) and [[Sigmaringen]] (1863).
