{{Infobox company | name = | logo = 2009 MDDUS Logo.jpg | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = en | former_name = | type = | industry = | founded = {{start date|1902|05|df=yes}} in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]] | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location = | hq_location_city = | hq_location_country = | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = [[professional indemnity]] | brands = | services = | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | website = {{URL|http://www.mddus.com}} }} The '''Medical and Dental Defence Union of Scotland''' ('''MDDUS''') is one of three major medical defence organisations (MDOs) in the UK and offers [[professional indemnity]] and expert medico-legal and dento-legal advice for doctors, dentists and other healthcare professionals throughout the [[United Kingdom]]. MDDUS is a mutual organisation and was founded in 1902.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/healthcare-network/2013/jun/28/day-life-ceo-medical-dental-defence-body-mddus |title=A day in the life of ... the chief executive of a medical and dental defence body |first=Gordon |last=Dickson |work=The Guardian |date=28 June 2013 |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> It is recognised by the UK's [[General Medical Council]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gmc-uk.org/doctors/information_for_doctors/medical_defense_organisations.asp |title=Information for doctors who are on the register: Medico-legal support |publisher=[[General Medical Council]] |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>
Competitors include Premium Medical Protection, or PMP, the [[Medical Protection Society]], or MPS, and the [[Medical Defence Union]], or MDU.
At the [[University of Glasgow]], the MDDUS offers the prestigious "Medical and Dental Defence Union of Scotland Prize for Medical Jurisprudence" annually.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/award/?id=638 |title=Awards: Medical and Dental Defence Union of Scotland Prize (Medical Jurisprudence) |publisher=[[University of Glasgow]] |accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>
